Enables the events from JLayer and all its descendants defined by the specified event mask parameter to be delivered to the LayerUI.eventDispatched(AWTEvent, JLayer) method. Events are delivered provided that LayerUI is set for this JLayer and the JLayer is displayable. The following example shows how to correctly use this method in the LayerUI implementations:     public void installUI(JComponent c) {
       super.installUI(c);
       JLayer l = (JLayer) c;
       // this LayerUI will receive only key and focus events
       l.setLayerEventMask(AWTEvent.KEY_EVENT_MASK | AWTEvent.FOCUS_EVENT_MASK);
    }

    public void uninstallUI(JComponent c) {
       super.uninstallUI(c);
       JLayer l = (JLayer) c;
       // JLayer must be returned to its initial state
       l.setLayerEventMask(0);
    }
 By default JLayer receives no events and its event mask is 0.
